HEADWORD: Arteriotomy
<hw>Ar*te`ri*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arteriotomia</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ + <?/ a cutting.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The opening of an artery, esp. for
bloodletting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That part of anatomy which treats of the dissection
